{"word":"Machir","slug":"machir","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Machir</b> <a href=\"#/H4353\">H4353</a> <br/> 1. One of the sons of Manasseh:<br/> - General references<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=50&verse=23'>Gen 50:23</a> <br/> - Father of the Machirites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=26&verse=29'>Num 26:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=36&verse=1'>Num 36:1</a> <br/> - The land of Gilead allotted to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=32&verse=40'>Num 32:40</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=3&verse=15'>Deu 3:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=13&verse=31'>Jos 13:31</a> <br/> - Certain cities of Bashan given to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=13&verse=31'>Jos 13:31</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=17&verse=1'>Jos 17:1</a> <br/> 2. A man of Lo-Debar who took care of Jonathan's lame son, Mephibosheth<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=9&verse=5'>2Sa 9:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=17&verse=27'>2Sa 17:27</a>"}]}